title: Top-10 finishing order after Stage 2 at Atlanta Motor Speedway

persons.name: mark j. rebilas mark j. rebilas-usa

text:
Mar 5, 2017 at 4:35p ET 0Shares 
The first stage of the Folds of Honor QuikTrip 500 at Atlanta Motor Speedway has come to a close at Lap 170. 
Check out the top-10 finishers who receive points at the end of Stage 2: Shanna Lockwood Shanna Lockwood-USA TODAY Sports 1 Kevin Harvick, 10 (1 playoff point) 
Harvick dominated through the first two stages of the race and grabbed his second stage win on Lap 170. Getty Images Getty Images 2 Chase Elliott, 9 
Elliott has appeared to have one of the best cars in the field next to the No. 4 Ford. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 3 Ryan Newman, 8 
Newman started on the outside row and battled his way back into the top-5 in the second stage. Mark J. Rebilas Mark J. Rebilas-USA TODAY Sports 4 
Truex Jr. grabbed more points in Stage 2 after finishing top 10 in Stage 1. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Lesley Ann Miller 5 Kyle Larson, 6 
Larson has been around the top of the field all day, grabbing more stage points at the close of Stage 2. Shanna Lockwood Shanna Lockwood-USA TODAY Sports 6 Austin Dillon, 5 
Dillon just missed grabbed points at the end of Stage 1, but battled into the top 10 for the second stage. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Barry Cantrell 7 Brad Keselowski, 4 
Keselowski used unorthodox pit strategy to get into the top 10 at the end of Stage 2. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Matthew T. Thacker 8 
The rookie driver has patiently moved his way up through the field all day. 9 Clint Bowyer, 2 
Bowyer looks to rebound after a rough go at Daytona, heâ€™s coming on stronger as the day goes on in Atlanta. 10 Trevor Bayne, 1 
Bayne rounds out the top 10 for Stage 2 and has a solid Roush Fenway Racing Ford. Jerome Miron Jerome Miron-USA TODAY Sports
